======================================================================
OCF VERIFICATION: DIRECTED CYCLES vs VERTEX SETS
======================================================================

  The definition says: 'vertices are directed odd cycles of T'
  So each DISTINCT directed cycle is a separate vertex of ő©(T).
  For 3-cycles: 1 directed cycle per vertex set (in a tournament).
  For 5-cycles: MULTIPLE directed cycles possible per vertex set!

======================================================================
EXHAUSTIVE n=5: BOTH INTERPRETATIONS
======================================================================

  Vertex-set method: 184/1024 mismatches
  Directed-cycle method: 0/1024 mismatches

  DIRECTED CYCLE method is correct!
  Must count distinct directed cycles, not just vertex sets.

